<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 4:32PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Warren
and northwestern Halifax Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 432 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Littleton, or 7 miles west of Roanoke Rapids, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke Rapids, Halifax, Littleton, Enfield, Weldon, South Weldon,
Airlie, Rosemary, Roanoke Rapids Lake and Medoc Mountain State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
